WHAT THIS IS

This is bgav, a multimedia decoding library. It it primarly a support
library for gmerlin, but it can also be used as a standalone library for
getting sophisticated media file decoding support for your application.

It needs gavl, the support library for handling uncompressed audio-
and video data.

In the include directory, you'll find the headers. The public API
is in bgav.h. You might also take a look at the gavl headers for the
definition of the AV-formats and -frames.

The API is damn simple: look at tests/bgavdump.c. This program dumps all
informations, it can find about a media file onto stderr. After that, it
tries to decode one frame of each audio- or video stream.

For further information, you can also consult plugins/i_avdec.c, which is
the actual gmerlin plugin.

REQUIREMENTS:

The configure script autodetects all installed libraries.

* Latest ffmpeg with shared library support. Download ffmpeg, unpack the
  source and do ./configure --enable-shared; make install
  It is stronly recommended to install this, otherwise you won't be able to
  decode much.

* Ogg Vorbis libraries from http://www.vorbis.com

* FAAD from http://www.audiocoding.com

* Win32 codecs. Go to http://mplayerhq.hu and download
  the files win32codecs.tar.bz2 and qt5dlls.tar.bz2. All
  codec dlls must be in /usr/lib/win32

* You can also get the xanim 3ivx codec from http://www.3ivx.com.
  Copy the dll file (vid_3ivX.xa) to a directory and let the
  XANIM_MOD_DIR environment variable point to it.

* libmpeg2 from libmpeg2.sourceforge.net

* liba52 from liba52.sourceforge.net

SUPPORTED DATA SOURCES:

* Regular files

* pnm Protocol used by older Real servers

* mms protocol (Windows media)

* rtsp with RealMedia RDP

* http with icecast (mp3 and Vorbis) and shoutcast support

SUPPORTED FORMATS:

* AVI
* ASF (aka WMV, WMA)
* Quicktime
* RealMedia (.rm)
* WAV
+ mp4
* aiff
* au
* Real Audio (.ra) (todo)
* Raw mp3
* Mpeg-1/2 System streams

